## Decisions Log

Record architectural choices here as they are made so neither of us has to re-derive them.

| Date | Decision | Rationale |
|------|----------|-----------|
| 2026-03-06 | NV-DINOv2 ViT-L via NIM API for scene embedding | Start with ViT-L (1024d/image, 4096d scene). Upgrade to ViT-G (1536d, 6144d) via env var swap if quality insufficient. NIM API keeps access pattern consistent with description and debate agents. |
| 2026-03-06 | NIM API for embedding (not local GPU) | Eliminates CUDA dependency for embedding step. T4 reserved for optional future local TRT deployment. |
| 2026-03-06 | 4 cameras per scene: CAM_F0, CAM_L0, CAM_R0, CAM_B0 | Matches nuPlan mini camera layout. Concatenated embedding captures full surround context. |
| 2026-03-08 | Streamlit for v0 frontend (not Next.js) | Faster to ship for demo. Migrate to Next.js for production if needed. |
| 2026-03-08 | Regression suite uses NIM text embedding (nv-embedqa-e5-v5) | Scene embeddings (NV-DINOv2) are image-based; regression suite is text-based. Different embedding models, same pgvector storage. |
| 2026-03-08 | Contrastive scene description (FLAGGED + nearest TYPICAL neighbor) | Send both flagged medoid images and nearest non-anomalous neighbor images to NIM vision so the model can compare-and-contrast and produce a grounded description + contrast_rationale. Aligns description with embedding-space anomaly signal; prompts separate benign vs risk-relevant differences. |

